# Simplicity first (highest priority)

When adding or changing any file in this repo:

- Prefer the **shortest** correct solution: fewest abstractions, fewest new files, shallowest call stack.
- **No** extra comments, doc blocks, or README churn unless the user asks.
- **No** drive-by refactors, “cleanup” in unrelated files, or defensive layers unless required for the task.
- Match existing patterns; if something can be one function or one component, keep it one.
- Korean or English in UI copy is fine; **agent-facing** text (rules, AGENTS) stays terse.

If a trade-off appears, choose **simpler** over clever.
